The paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing shortest paths on networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from Network Information Theory (cs.NI) and Algorithmic Game Theory (cs.GT) to achieve its results. Additionally, the paper mentions ruling sets, which is a classic algorithmic technique in theoretical computer science (cs.AL).
